wiki.content: “Earth” is an environmental awareness song, released three days before Earth Day in 2019, about the dangers that climate change has on our planet and its ecosystems. During an interview on The Ellen Show, Lil Dicky revealed the track features over 30 artists, with each of them taking on the roles of a different animal. For example, Justin Bieber plays on the role of a baboon, Ariana Grande takes on the role of a zebra, and Ed Sheeran plays a koala bear. Dave went on to describe the meaning of this song on The Ellen Show by saying: "I mean honestly when I started making this song I didn’t know the details or the facts at hand. But like we have 12 years to change the way we do so many things on earth, or the damage is irreversible. And within our lifetime, well within our lifetime, crazy things are gonna happen. Floods, food shortages, bad air, millions of people relocated… It’s like… very soon." It was also announced that proceeds from this song and video will be going towards the Leonardo DiCaprio Foundation, which fights to help protect vulnerable wildlife from extinction.
